text: As a new father, I can't imagine the Parkland community's heartbreak. No matter who you are, we all want the same thing: a safer world for our children. I hope through thoughtful debate we can arrive at policy solutions that increase the safety and freedom of all Americans.

The Fostering Innovation Act will right-size the regulatory environment that detracts from medical advancements, enabling America to develop the next generation of cures to combat illnesses that plague Hoosiers. #IN09
Today, the House is voting on the Fostering Innovation Act, which I introduced with @RepSinema to ensure that costly regulations don’t stand in the way of successful biopharmaceutical research.
I just read the @HouseIntelComm memo; this report needs to be released. Americans deserve truth and transparency, two key pillars of our country’s democracy. #ReleaseTheMemo

Every day, our police officers like John are always there to keep our communities safe. To all Hoosier law enforcement officers, on Law Enforcement Appreciation Day and every day, thank you for your service. #LawEnforcementAppreciationDay
1/ Attn Veterans in Clark County: your Congressional office casework team will be at the Veterans' Stand Down event in Jeffersonville today.
Members of my staff will be present at Harrison County's Annual Stand Down tomorrow at Lincoln Hills Christian Church from 10a to 2p.
Linking bad legislative tricks to disaster recovery is not only bad government, it is immoral and the American people deserve better. 4/4
The CR & Debt Ceiling package created by the U.S. Senate ignores expectation that our gov plans for the future like we do here at home. 3/4
What I voted against today was Washington, D.C.’s style of “problem-solving” ... the exact opposite of what Hoosiers demanded last Nov. 2/4
On Wednesday, I voted for a clean disaster aid package b/c I do believe that we should help our neighbors when they need it most. 1/4
Pleased @POTUS ended rule denying local police access to surplus lifesaving equipment. Local police now have access to much needed tools.
Please join me in keeping the City of Salem's Police Chief in our thoughts and prayers as he recovers from emergency surgery.
The bigotry demonstrated in #Charlottesville does not represent our great nation & must be condemned. Prayers to those injured or killed.
My thoughts & prayers are with Majority Whip @SteveScalise, the @CapitolPolice, & staff who were affected by the horrific shooting today.
Congrats to the Eastern Lady Musketeers of Pekin on winning the Indiana Girl's Basketball 2A State Championship today! cc: @ehsmusketeers
Obama Administration developed a rule that limited options for small investors. @POTUS returned those options today w/ his Executive Order.
We need to return the Supreme Court to the role our Founders envisioned; the new #SCOTUS can return the Court to its rightful place.
It was a packed day, but we’re just getting started. I look forward to criss-crossing #IN09 multiple times in the coming months (10/10)
I ended the day w/ the @TownClarksville honoring two officers from Clarksville Police Dept. who had been named Officers of the Year. (7/10)
Yesterday was a busy day meeting w/ constituents & small business owners across #IN09! Started by meeting w/ Mayor Merry in Salem, IN (1/10)
On Sundays, my family gathers to complete an afternoon of community service. Today, we spent time at a local food kitchen.
Obamacare has failed the American people: options have reduced and premiums have skyrocketed. Now is the time for #FullRepeal.
Today, I introduced my first piece of legislation: a Constitutional Amendment in favor of #TermLimits for Members of Congress.
Congratulations to @realDonaldTrump & @mike_pence on being certified the next President and Vice President by a Joint Session of Congress.
I'm honored that my colleagues have selected me to serve on @FinancialCmte. Together, we will reduce the burden of federal regulations!
Officially a member of the #115thCongress! I am excited to get to work for the Hoosiers of #IN09!
